&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Director, Patient-Reported Outcomes (PRO) and Preference Elicitation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking motivated and experienced professionals to join our HEOR team as a Director, focusing on Patient-Reported Outcomes (PRO) and Preference Elicitation Studies. You will contribute to groundbreaking projects that influence healthcare decision-making, advancing the understanding of patient perspectives and preferences to enhance value-driven healthcare delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic leadership in the design and delivery of PRO and preference elicitation research.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive innovation in preference elicitation methodologies and PRO development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape evidence generation strategies to support HTA submissions and payer negotiations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and develop a team of professionals, fostering expertise in PRO and preference elicitation studies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and manage client relationships, contributing to business development through proposal preparation and thought leadership activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other HEOR functions, including health economic modelling and real-world evidence, to deliver integrated solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Desired Skills and Experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced degree (PhD or MSc) in Health Economics, Epidemiology, Medical Sciences, Psychology, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Minimum of 7-8 years of experience&lt;/u&gt;, with a strong track record in PRO and preference elicitation studies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable expertise in designing and conducting qualitative and/or quantitative research for PRO and preference elicitation studies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of methodologies for utility measurement, survey development, and psychometric validation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong skills in statistical analysis, econometrics, and data interpretation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with experience publishing in peer-reviewed journals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to manage projects, teams, and client relationships effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with advanced statistical methods, survey platforms (e.g., Qualtrics), and coding languages (e.g., HTML, JavaScript).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with HTA environments and global payer requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of innovative methodologies in preference elicitation, such as discrete choice experiments and best-worst scaling.&lt;/li&gt;
