&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To support a range of quantitative and qualitative and health economics and outcomes research projects, including health valuation and utility measurement, analysis of outcomes data and development of patient-reported outcome measures for our valued clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The focus of the role is on patient-reported outcome measurement and preference elicitation research.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Desired Skills and Experience&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Functional technical expertise&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educational degree (such as MSc) in in Health Economics, Epidemiology, Medical Sciences, Psychology, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 1-3 years of experience, with a strong track record in PRO and preference elicitation studies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of health economics and methodologies for the analysis of patient-reported outcomes (e.g., utility measurement, analysis and development of patient reported outcome measures)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of methodologies for utility measurement, survey development, and psychometric validation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of statistical analysis, econometrics, and data interpretation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good knowledge of statistical software packages (e.g., Stata, R)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent MS Word, Outlook, PowerPoint, and Excel skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Communication skills&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to clearly communicate technical issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Other desirable attributes &amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to contribute towards non-project related work for PHMR&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great to work with as part of a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work autonomously when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;What we offer you!&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility and individual support for more balanced and enjoyable life&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive compensation packages and great benefits&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fantastic opportunities for professional development, working along industry experts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tight-knit, collegiate office environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid working model - offering flexibility to work from home weekly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This role can sit in a range of places - London, Newcastle, or Ireland [please rank office location preferences in our application form]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
