&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Position Overview&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Putnam is looking to hire a Senior Consultant to join our HTA (Health Technology Assessment) and Market Access group. In this role you will help lead the development and execution of market access strategies across Germany and Europe, with a strong focus on HTA submissions (e.g., AMNOG, JCA), pricing, and reimbursement. The role combines strategic leadership, technical expertise, and client-facing responsibilities across the full product lifecycle—from evidence generation to price negotiations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Market Access Strategy &amp;amp; HTA Leadership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead preparation and delivery of HTA dossiers (must have hands on AMNOG submission experience and ideally EU JCA) from early strategy through to price negotiations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise clients on pricing, reimbursement, and market access strategies across Europe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support early access programs and scientific advice consultations for clinical development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Health Economics &amp;amp; Evidence Generation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and oversee HEOR studies, including methodology, analysis, and interpretation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate clinical and economic evidence into clear, impactful insights for stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Client &amp;amp; Project Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage projects end-to-end (scope, timeline, budget, quality)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a trusted advisor in client engagements, including interactions with regulatory and payer bodies (e.g., GKV-Spitzenverband)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thought Leadership &amp;amp; Deliverables&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and review protocols, reports, presentations, and HTA documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to publications (abstracts, manuscripts)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and apply evolving HTA and health economics methodologies, particularly in Germany/EU&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
