&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced degree in life sciences, pharmacy, health economics, or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;~3+ years’ experience in HTA, pricing &amp;amp; reimbursement, and HEOR across multiple markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record leading HTA submissions and market access projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of European payer systems and HTA processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in client management and proposal development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical, quantitative, and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills (ability to simplify complex topics)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive, collaborative, and solutions-oriented mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in statistical tools, MS Office, and digital/AI-supported workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in English and German &lt;/li&gt;
